    <remarks>Also, the presence/absence of Pos, UserPos, and UserSize is significant, though they don't directly refer to GdkGeometry fields. UserPos will be set automatically by GtkWindow if you call <see cref="M:Gtk.Window.Move" />. UserPos and UserSize should be set if the user specified a size/position using a --geometry command-line argument; <see cref="M:Gtk.Window.ParseGeometry" /> automatically sets these flags.</remarks>
